32// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
33// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
34// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
35// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
36// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
37#if defined(BUILDING_V8_SHARED) && defined(USING_V8_SHARED)
38#error both BUILDING_V8_SHARED and USING_V8_SHARED are set - please check the\
39 build configuration to ensure that at most one of these is set
40#endif
41
42#ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
43# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
44#elif USING_V8_SHARED
45# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
46#else
47# define V8_EXPORT
48#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
49
50#else // V8_OS_WIN
51
52// Setup for Linux shared library export.
53#if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY && defined(V8_SHARED)
54# ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
55# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
56# else
57# define V8_EXPORT
58# endif
59#else
60# define V8_EXPORT
61#endif

63#endif // V8_OS_WIN

163class UniqueId {
164 public:
165 explicit UniqueId(intptr_t data)
166 : data_(data) {}
167
168 bool operator==(const UniqueId& other) const {
169 return data_ == other.data_;
170 }
171
172 bool operator!=(const UniqueId& other) const {
173 return data_ != other.data_;
174 }
175
176 bool operator<(const UniqueId& other) const {
177 return data_ < other.data_;
178 }
179
180 private:
181 intptr_t data_;
182};

186#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
187 while (false) { \
188 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
189 }

217template <class T>
218class Local {
219 public:
220 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
221 template <class S>
222 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
223 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
229 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
230 }
231
235 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
236
240 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
241
242 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
243
244 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
245
252 template <class S>
253 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
254 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
255 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
256 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
257 if (b == 0) return false;
258 return *a == *b;
259 }
260
261 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
262 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
263 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
264 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
265 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
266 if (b == 0) return false;
267 return *a == *b;
268 }
269
276 template <class S>
277 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
278 return !operator==(that);
279 }
280
281 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
282 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
283 return !operator==(that);
284 }
285
286 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
287#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
288 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
289 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
290 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
291#endif
292 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
293 }
294
295
296 template <class S> V8_INLINE Local<S> As() {
297 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
298 }
299
305 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
306 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
307 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
308
309 private:
310 friend class Utils;
311 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
312 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
313 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
314 template<class F> friend class Local;
315 template <class F>
316 friend class MaybeLocal;
317 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
318 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
319 friend class String;
320 friend class Object;
321 friend class Context;
322 friend class Private;
323 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
324 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
325 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
326 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
327 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
328 friend class HandleScope;
329 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
330 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
331 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
332 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
333 template <class F>
334 friend class ReturnValue;
335
336 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
337 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
338 T* val_;
339};

359template <class T>
360class MaybeLocal {
361 public:
362 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
363 template <class S>
364 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
365 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
366 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
367 }
368
369 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
370
371 template <class S>
372 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
373 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
374 return !IsEmpty();
375 }
376
377 // Will crash if the MaybeLocal<> is empty.
378 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
379
380 template <class S>
381 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
382 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
383 }
384
385 private:
386 T* val_;
387};

390// Eternal handles are set-once handles that live for the life of the isolate.
391template <class T> class Eternal {
392 public:
393 V8_INLINE Eternal() : index_(kInitialValue) { }
394 template<class S>
395 V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : index_(kInitialValue) {
396 Set(isolate, handle);
397 }
398 // Can only be safely called if already set.
399 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate);
400 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() { return index_ == kInitialValue; }
401 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
402
403 private:
404 static const int kInitialValue = -1;
405 int index_;
406};

409static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
410
411
412template <typename T>
413class WeakCallbackInfo {
414 public:
415 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
416
417 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
418 void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
419 Callback* callback)
420 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
421 for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
422 internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
423 }
424 }
425
426 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
427 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
428 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
429
430 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
431 void* GetInternalField1() const) {
432 return internal_fields_[0];
433 }
434 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
435 void* GetInternalField2() const) {
436 return internal_fields_[1];
437 }
438
439 V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
440 bool IsFirstPass() const) {
441 return callback_ != nullptr;
442 }
443
444 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
445 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
446 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
447 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
448 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
449 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
450 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
451
452 private:
453 Isolate* isolate_;
454 T* parameter_;
455 Callback* callback_;
456 void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
457};

460template <class T, class P>
461class WeakCallbackData {
462 public:
463 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackData<T, P>& data);
464
465 WeakCallbackData(Isolate* isolate, P* parameter, Local<T> handle)
466 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), handle_(handle) {}
467
468 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
469 V8_INLINE P* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
470 V8_INLINE Local<T> GetValue() const { return handle_; }
471
472 private:
473 Isolate* isolate_;
474 P* parameter_;
475 Local<T> handle_;
476};

500template <class T> class PersistentBase {
501 public:
506 V8_INLINE void Reset();
511 template <class S>
512 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
513
518 template <class S>
519 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
520
521 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == NULL; }
522 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
523
524 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
525 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
526 }
527
528 template <class S>
529 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
530 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
531 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
532 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
533 if (b == NULL) return false;
534 return *a == *b;
535 }
536
537 template <class S>
538 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
539 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
540 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
541 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
542 if (b == NULL) return false;
543 return *a == *b;
544 }
545
546 template <class S>
547 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
548 return !operator==(that);
549 }
550
551 template <class S>
552 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
553 return !operator==(that);
554 }
555
563 template <typename P>
564 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED(
565 "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
566 void SetWeak(P* parameter,
567 typename WeakCallbackData<T, P>::Callback callback));
568
569 template <typename S, typename P>
570 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED(
571 "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
572 void SetWeak(P* parameter,
573 typename WeakCallbackData<S, P>::Callback callback));
574
575 // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
576 // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
577 // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects
578 // it references transitively in one GC cycle. At the moment you can either
579 // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
580 // fields in the dying object.
581 template <typename P>
582 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED(
583 "use SetWeak",
584 void SetPhantom(P* parameter,
585 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
586 int internal_field_index1 = -1,
587 int internal_field_index2 = -1));
588
589 template <typename P>
590 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
591 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
592 WeakCallbackType type);
593
594 template<typename P>
595 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
596
597 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
598 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
599
605 V8_INLINE void RegisterExternalReference(Isolate* isolate);
606
613 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();
614
623 V8_INLINE void MarkPartiallyDependent();
624
630 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();
631
632 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;
633
635 V8_INLINE bool IsNearDeath() const;
636
638 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
639
644 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
645
650 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
651
652 private:
653 friend class Isolate;
654 friend class Utils;
655 template<class F> friend class Local;
656 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
657 template <class F>
658 friend class Global;
659 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
660 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
661 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
662 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
663 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
664 friend class Object;
665
666 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
667 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
668 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
669 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
670
671 T* val_;
672};

722template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
723 public:
727 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
733 template <class S>
734 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
735 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
736 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
737 }
743 template <class S, class M2>
744 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
745 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
746 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
747 }
754 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
755 Copy(that);
756 }
757 template <class S, class M2>
758 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
759 Copy(that);
760 }
761 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
762 Copy(that);
763 return *this;
764 }
765 template <class S, class M2>
766 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
767 Copy(that);
768 return *this;
769 }
775 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
776 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
777 }
778
779 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
780 template <class S>
781 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
782#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
783 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
784 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
785 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
786#endif
787 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(that);
788 }
789
790 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
791 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() { // NOLINT
792 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
793 }
794
795 private:
796 friend class Isolate;
797 friend class Utils;
798 template<class F> friend class Local;
799 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
800 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
801
802 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
803 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
804 template<class S, class M2>
805 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
806};

814template <class T>
815class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
816 public:
820 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
826 template <class S>
827 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
828 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
829 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
830 }
836 template <class S>
837 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
838 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
839 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
840 }
844 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
845 other.val_ = nullptr;
846 }
847 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
851 template <class S>
852 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
853 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
854 if (this != &rhs) {
855 this->Reset();
856 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
857 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
858 }
859 return *this;
860 }
864 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
865
866 /*
867 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
868 */
869 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
870
871 private:
872 template <class F>
873 friend class ReturnValue;
874 Global(const Global&) = delete;
875 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
876 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
877};

1015class ScriptOriginOptions {
1016 public:
1017 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_embedder_debug_script = false,
1018 bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1019 bool is_opaque = false)
1020 : flags_((is_embedder_debug_script ? kIsEmbedderDebugScript : 0) |
1021 (is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1022 (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0)) {}
1023 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1024 : flags_(flags &
1025 (kIsEmbedderDebugScript | kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque)) {}
1026 bool IsEmbedderDebugScript() const {
1027 return (flags_ & kIsEmbedderDebugScript) != 0;
1028 }
1029 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1030 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1031 }
1032 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1033 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1034
1035 private:
1036 enum {
1037 kIsEmbedderDebugScript = 1,
1038 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1 << 1,
1039 kIsOpaque = 1 << 2
1040 };
1041 const int flags_;
1042};

1149class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1150 public:
1158 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1159 enum BufferPolicy {
1160 BufferNotOwned,
1161 BufferOwned
1162 };
1163
1164 CachedData()
1165 : data(NULL),
1166 length(0),
1167 rejected(false),
1168 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1169
1170 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1171 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1172 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1173 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1174 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1175 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1176 ~CachedData();
1177 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1178 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1179 const uint8_t* data;
1180 int length;
1181 bool rejected;
1182 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1183
1184 private:
1185 // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1186 CachedData(const CachedData&);
1187 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&);
1188 };
1189
1193 class Source {
1194 public:

1197 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1198 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1199 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1200 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1201
1202 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1203 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1204 // alive.
1205 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1206
1207 private:
1208 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1209 // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1210 Source(const Source&);
1211 Source& operator=(const Source&);
1212
1213 Local<String> source_string;
1214
1215 // Origin information
1216 Local<Value> resource_name;
1217 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1218 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1219 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;

1222 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1223 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1224 // set when calling a compile method.
1225 CachedData* cached_data;
1226 };

2477class V8_EXPORT Symbol : public Name {
2478 public:
2479 // Returns the print name string of the symbol, or undefined if none.
2480 Local<Value> Name() const;
2481
2482 // Create a symbol. If name is not empty, it will be used as the description.
2483 static Local<Symbol> New(Isolate* isolate,
2484 Local<String> name = Local<String>());
2485
2486 // Access global symbol registry.
2487 // Note that symbols created this way are never collected, so
2488 // they should only be used for statically fixed properties.
2489 // Also, there is only one global name space for the names used as keys.
2490 // To minimize the potential for clashes, use qualified names as keys.
2491 static Local<Symbol> For(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2492
2493 // Retrieve a global symbol. Similar to |For|, but using a separate
2494 // registry that is not accessible by (and cannot clash with) JavaScript code.
2495 static Local<Symbol> ForApi(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2496
2497 // Well-known symbols
2498 static Local<Symbol> GetIterator(Isolate* isolate);
2499 static Local<Symbol> GetUnscopables(Isolate* isolate);
2500 static Local<Symbol> GetToStringTag(Isolate* isolate);
2501 static Local<Symbol> GetIsConcatSpreadable(Isolate* isolate);
2502
2503 V8_INLINE static Symbol* Cast(v8::Value* obj);
2504
2505 private:
2506 Symbol();
2507 static void CheckCast(v8::Value* obj);
2508};

3116template<typename T>
3117class ReturnValue {
3118 public:
3119 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3120 : value_(that.value_) {
3121 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3122 }
3123 // Local setters
3124 template <typename S>
3125 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3126 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3127 template <typename S>
3128 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3129 template <typename S>
3130 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3131 // Fast primitive setters
3132 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3133 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3134 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3135 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3136 // Fast JS primitive setters
3137 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3138 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3139 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3140 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3141 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3142
3143 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3144 template <typename S>
3145 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3146
3147 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3148 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3149 // value.
3150 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3151
3152 private:
3153 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3154 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3155 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3156 template <class F, class G, class H>
3157 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3158 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3159 V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3160 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3161 internal::Object** value_;
3162};

4583enum class PropertyHandlerFlags {
4584 kNone = 0,
4585 // See ALL_CAN_READ above.
4586 kAllCanRead = 1,
4587 // Will not call into interceptor for properties on the receiver or prototype
4588 // chain. Currently only valid for named interceptors.
4589 kNonMasking = 1 << 1,
4590 // Will not call into interceptor for symbol lookup. Only meaningful for
4591 // named interceptors.
4592 kOnlyInterceptStrings = 1 << 2,
4593};

4596struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
4597 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
4599 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter = 0,
4600 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter = 0,
4601 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query = 0,
4602 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = 0,
4603 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = 0,
4604 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
4605 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
4606 : getter(getter),
4607 setter(setter),
4608 query(query),
4609 deleter(deleter),
4610 enumerator(enumerator),
4611 data(data),
4612 flags(flags) {}
4613
4614 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter;
4615 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter;
4616 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query;
4617 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter;
4618 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator;
4619 Local<Value> data;
4620 PropertyHandlerFlags flags;
4621};

5292struct JitCodeEvent {
5293 enum EventType {
5294 CODE_ADDED,
5295 CODE_MOVED,
5296 CODE_REMOVED,
5297 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
5298 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
5299 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
5300 };
5301 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
5302 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
5303 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
5304 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
5305 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
5306 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
5307
5308 // Type of event.
5309 EventType type;
5310 // Start of the instructions.
5311 void* code_start;
5312 // Size of the instructions.
5313 size_t code_len;
5314 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
5315 Local<UnboundScript> script;
5316 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
5317 // code line information which is returned from the
5318 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
5319 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
5320 void* user_data;
5321
5322 struct name_t {
5323 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
5324 // zero-terminated.
5325 const char* str;
5326 // Number of chars in str.
5327 size_t len;
5328 };
5329
5330 struct line_info_t {
5331 // PC offset
5332 size_t offset;
5333 // Code postion
5334 size_t pos;
5335 // The position type.
5336 PositionType position_type;
5337 };
5338
5339 union {
5340 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
5341 struct name_t name;
5342
5343 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
5344 struct line_info_t line_info;
5345
5346 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
5347 void* new_code_start;
5348 };
5349};
5350
5354enum JitCodeEventOptions {
5355 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
5356 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
5357 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
5358};
5359

5366typedef void (*JitCodeEventHandler)(const JitCodeEvent* event);

6712template <class T>
6713class Maybe {
6714 public:
6715 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6716 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6717
6718 // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6719 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6720 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6721 return value;
6722 }
6723
6724 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6725 return has_value ? value : default_value;
6726 }
6727
6728 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6729 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6730 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6731 }
6732
6733 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6734 return !operator==(other);
6735 }
6736
6737 private:
6738 Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6739 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6740
6741 bool has_value;
6742 T value;
6743
6744 template <class U>
6745 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6746 template <class U>
6747 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6748};
6749
6750
6751template <class T>
6752inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6753 return Maybe<T>();
6754}
6755
6756
6757template <class T>
6758inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6759 return Maybe<T>(t);
6760}

7248namespace internal {
7249
7250const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
7251const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
7252const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
7253
7254// Tag information for HeapObject.
7255const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
7256const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
7257const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
7258
7259// Tag information for Smi.
7260const int kSmiTag = 0;
7261const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
7262const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
7263
7264template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
7265
7266template<int kSmiShiftSize>
7267V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7268 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7269 uintptr_t tagged_value =
7270 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
7271 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
7272}
7273
7274// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
7275template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
7276 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
7277 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7278 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7279 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7280 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7281 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
7282 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
7283 }
7284 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7285 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7286 }
7287 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7288 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
7289 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
7290 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
7291 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
7292 //
7293 // CAUTION: The original code below:
7294 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
7295 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
7296 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
7297 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
7298 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
7299 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
7300 }
7301};
7302
7303// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
7304template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
7305 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
7306 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7307 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7308 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7309 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7310 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
7311 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
7312 }
7313 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7314 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7315 }
7316 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7317 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
7318 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
7319 }
7320};
7321
7322typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
7323const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
7324const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
7325V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
7326V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

7392 V8_EXPORT static void CheckInitializedImpl(v8::Isolate* isolate);
7393 V8_INLINE static void CheckInitialized(v8::Isolate* isolate) {
7394#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7395 CheckInitializedImpl(isolate);
7396#endif
7397 }
7398
7399 V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
7400 return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
7401 kHeapObjectTag);
7402 }
7403
7404 V8_INLINE static int SmiValue(const internal::Object* value) {
7405 return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);
7406 }
7407
7408 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7409 return PlatformSmiTagging::IntToSmi(value);
7410 }
7411
7412 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7413 return PlatformSmiTagging::IsValidSmi(value);
7414 }
7415
7416 V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
7417 typedef internal::Object O;
7418 O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
7419 // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
7420 // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
7421 return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
7422 }
7423
7424 V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
7425 typedef internal::Object O;
7426 return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
7427 }
7428
7429 V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
7430 int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
7431 return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
7432 }
7433
7434 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
7435 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7436 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
7437 }
7438
7439 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
7440 bool value, int shift) {
7441 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7442 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
7443 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
7444 }
7445
7446 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
7447 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7448 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
7449 }
7450
7451 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
7452 uint8_t value) {
7453 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7454 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
7455 }
7456
7457 V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
7458 uint32_t slot,
7459 void* data) {
7460 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
7461 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
7462 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
7463 }
7464
7465 V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
7466 uint32_t slot) {
7467 const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
7468 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
7469 return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
7470 }
7471
7472 V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
7473 int index) {
7474 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
7475 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
7476 }
7477
7478 template <typename T>
7479 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
7480 const uint8_t* addr =
7481 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
7482 return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
7483 }
7484
7485 template <typename T>
7486 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
7487 typedef internal::Object O;
7488 typedef internal::Internals I;
7489 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
7490 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
7491 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
7492 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
7493 int value_offset =
7494 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7495 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
7496 }
7497};
7498
7499} // namespace internal

7588 typedef internal::Internals I;
7589 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
7590 uint8_t node_state =
7591 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
7592 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
7593 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
7594}

7602 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;

7785template<typename T>
7786void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
7787 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
7788 typedef internal::Internals I;
7789 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
7790 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
7791 return;
7792 }
7793 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
7794}
7795
7796template<typename T>
7797void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
7798 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
7799 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
7800 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
7801 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
7802 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
7803 return;
7804 }
7805 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
7806}
7807
7808template<typename T>
7809void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
7810 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
7811 typedef internal::Internals I;
7812 int root_index;
7813 if (value) {
7814 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
7815 } else {
7816 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
7817 }
7818 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
7819}

7822void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
7823 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
7824 typedef internal::Internals I;
7825 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
7826}

7830 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
7831 typedef internal::Internals I;
7832 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
7833}

7835template<typename T>

7837 TYPE_CHECK(T, String);
7838 typedef internal::Internals I;
7839 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
7840}

7848template <typename T>

7850 typedef internal::Internals I;
7851 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
7852 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
7853 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
7854}

8013
8014Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
8015#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8016 typedef internal::Object O;
8017 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
8018 typedef internal::Internals I;
8019 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8020 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8021 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8022 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
8023 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8024 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
8025 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
8026 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
8027 }
8028#endif
8029 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
8030}
8031
8032
8033void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
8034#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8035 typedef internal::Object O;
8036 typedef internal::Internals I;
8037 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8038 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8039 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8040 if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
8041 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8042 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
8043 }
8044#endif
8045 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
8046}

8056
8057Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {
8058 typedef internal::Object* S;
8059 typedef internal::Internals I;
8060 I::CheckInitialized(isolate);
8061 S* slot = I::GetRoot(isolate, I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
8062 return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
8063}

8065
8066String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
8067 typedef internal::Object O;
8068 typedef internal::Internals I;
8069 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
8070 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
8071 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
8072 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
8073 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
8074 } else {
8075 result = NULL;
8076 }
8077#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8078 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
8079#endif
8080 return result;
8081}
8082
8083
8084String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
8085 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
8086 typedef internal::Object O;
8087 typedef internal::Internals I;
8088 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
8089 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
8090 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
8091 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
8092 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
8093 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
8094 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
8095 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
8096 }
8097#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8098 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
8099#endif
8100 return resource;
8101}

8587
8588int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
8589 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
8590 typedef internal::Internals I;
8591 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
8592 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8593 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
8594 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
8595 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8596 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8597 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
8598 int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
8599 if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
8600 amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
8601 I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
8602 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
8603 }
8604 *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
8605 return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
8606}
